OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,GThe political drama of recent weeks has
OL,6,Gplaced enormous demands on journalists
OL,7,Gand broadcasters.
OL,9,FPolitical journalists have never known
OL,10,Fa time like this. There has never been
OL,11,Fa period in modern British politics
OL,12,Fwhen the authority of a new Prime
OL,13,FMinister whose party has a substantial
OL,14,Fmajority has been in question.
OL,16,FMeanwhile those whose specialism is in
OL,17,Fthe fields of business and economics
OL,18,Fhave been charged with explaining the
OL,19,Freaction to the mini budget.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G1/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34902
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FAll this comes against the backdrop of
OL,6,Fthe cost of living crisis, everyday
OL,7,Fpolitics and the recent escalation of
OL,8,Fthe war in Ukraine.
OL,10,FPerhaps this is a reminder of one of
OL,11,Fthe key differences between the BBC and
OL,12,Fthe main commercial public service
OL,13,Fbroadcasters.
OL,15,FIs news and current affairs at the very
OL,16,Fcentre of the organisation? Or is it
OL,17,Fsimply a public service obligation?
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G2/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34903
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FThe BBC is a unique organisation. One
OL,6,Fof its strengths is the diversity of
OL,7,Fits output and how it means different
OL,8,Fthings to different people.
OL,10,FIt would not be the organisation it is
OL,11,Fwithout Strictly, Frozen Planet, Doctor
OL,12,FWho or hidden gems like Thursday's
OL,13,Fbrilliant BBC Two documentary on TS
OL,14,FEliot.
OL,16,FNor would it be the same without Radio
OL,17,F2 or Blankety Blank. And it is vital
OL,18,Fthat EastEnders should either be
OL,19,Frestored to its former glory or retired
OL,20,Fwith dignity.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G3/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34904
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FAll those programmes in their different
OL,6,Fways mean a lot to different people.
OL,8,FThe BBC would be the weaker if it did
OL,9,Fnot try to provide a full range of
OL,10,Fprogrammes but there is no doubt about
OL,11,Fwhere the centre of gravity lies.
OL,13,FUltimately news and current affairs can
OL,14,Fbring down the director general as we
OL,15,Fhave seen twice in recent years.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G4/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34905
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FBut news cannot be a niche service  it
OL,6,Fhas to be at the heart of BBC One. The
OL,7,FBBC One bulletins tap into the
OL,8,Fexpertise of so many specialists who
OL,9,Fmight otherwise be contributing, say,
OL,10,Fto the BBC website or those niche
OL,11,Fprogrammes.
OL,13,FThe enormous audiences following the
OL,14,Fdeath of HM The Queen were proof of
OL,15,Fthis.
OL,17,FIn recent days, Breakfast and the main
OL,18,FBBC One bulletins have really lived up
OL,19,Fto the old adage of making "the good
OL,20,Fpopular and the popular good".
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G5/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34906
SC,0006
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FIt's worth remembering that the main
OL,6,Fnews programmes on BBC One all get some
OL,7,Fof the highest audience shares of the
OL,8,Fday and a significantly bigger audience
OL,9,Fthan their rivals on ITV  the BBC News
OL,10,Fat One beats its ITV counterpart 3-1.
OL,12,FGenerally the ratings pick up when the
OL,13,FBBC One bulletins start. This is still
OL,14,Fdespite the long-term decline of linear
OL,15,Faudiences.
OL,17,FMeanwhile on ITV, is the news the
OL,18,Fcentrepiece? Or is it merely a PSB
OL,19,Fobligation which also buys ITV
OL,20,Fcredibility and respectability?
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G6/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34907
SC,0007
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FThe excellence of ITN's journalism and
OL,6,Fthe quality of the main ITV News
OL,7,Fprogrammes is in no doubt. Indeed some
OL,8,FITV News journalists  notably Paul
OL,9,FBrand  made the running on some
OL,10,Fstories and left other broadcasters
OL,11,Fplaying catch up.
OL,13,FEarlier this year ITV took many by
OL,14,Fsurprise by doubling the regular
OL,15,Fduration of its main evening bulletin.
OL,16,FThe longer format has been a success.
OL,18,FBut twice this week the programme
OL,19,Freturned to a half hour duration 
OL,20,Fdespite the incredibly busy news
OL,21,Fagenda.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G7/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34908
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FThis risks giving the impression the
OL,6,Flonger news was simply opportune and a
OL,7,Fsensible commercial move  an excuse to
OL,8,Fstreamline the early evening schedule
OL,9,Fand avoid weak points.
OL,11,FAs is normal on a Friday, the bulletin
OL,12,Fonly lasted 30 minutes outside England.
OL,14,FMeanwhile  as ever  News at Ten can
OL,15,Ffloat around the schedule.
OL,17,FITV really needs to fully commit to
OL,18,Fmaintaining the duration of the 6.30pm
OL,19,Fbulletin if it is to fulfil its true
OL,20,Fpotential.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G8/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34909
SC,0009
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FAn hour on a quiet day? Half an hour in
OL,6,Fthe midst of a political crisis? This
OL,7,Fisn't fair on excellent journalists.
OL,9,FThe late evening news needs a fixed
OL,10,Fpoint too. It might even be better to
OL,11,Fabandon News at Ten and provide a
OL,12,Freliable berth at 10.30pm.
OL,14,FMeanwhile on 5, the main news runs
OL,15,Foutside peak time and attracts a modest
OL,16,Faudience.
OL,18,FA PSB obligation fulfilled but it
OL,19,Fhardly looks like the living heartbeat
OL,20,Fof the channel.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                  G9/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34910
SC,0010
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F349A1667854241
OL,5,FThe main news programmes on the two
OL,6,Fmain channels though are all very
OL,7,Fspecial and should never be taken for
OL,8,Fgranted. They attract wide audiences
OL,9,Fand are central to democratic life.
OL,11,FBut there is no doubt that on BBC One
OL,12,Fthe news is far, far more than a legal
OL,13,Fobligation or an exercise in corporate
OL,14,Fresponsibility.
OL,16,FITV the channel (not I stress ITN the
OL,17,Fnews provider) needs to be careful to
OL,18,Favoid inadvertently giving the
OL,19,Fimpression that its bulletins are not
OL,20,Falways cherished quite as they should
OL,21,Fbe.
OL,3,CAre BBC One and ITV equally as serious
OL,4,Cabout news?
OL,22,                                 G10/10
